---
import ProjectLayout from "../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro";
---

<ProjectLayout title="Locaperle - LLM-Scored Tenant Vetting">
  <h1 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Locaperle</h1>

  <div class="mb-4">
    <a
      href="https://locaperle.com"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      class="inline-flex items-center space-x-2 text-primary-400 hover:text-primary-300 font-mono font-semibold"
    >
      <svg
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        width="24"
        height="24"
        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        fill="none"
        stroke="currentColor"
        stroke-width="2"
        stroke-linecap="round"
        stroke-linejoin="round"
        class="w-5 h-5"
      >
        <path d="M5 12h14"></path>
        <path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7"></path>
      </svg>
      <span>→ locaperle.com</span>
    </a>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mt-2">Overview</h2>

  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Locaperle is an AI candidate-triage assistant for landlords re-letting flats. A Chrome
    extension captures incoming messages from rental platforms (LeBonCoin, Gens de Confiance),
    Gemini scores each candidate against a versioned eligibility rubric, and the landlord works
    from a ranked inbox — reviewing AI-drafted replies and sending them back to the platform
    without leaving the flow.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Core Capabilities</h2>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Message Capture Extension</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    A Chrome extension (Manifest V3) scrapes candidate messages, profiles, and listing details
    from rental platform messaging tabs in real time — no copy-pasting — and posts approved
    replies back to the platform.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">LLM Scoring Against Versioned Rubrics</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Each candidate gets a 0–100 solvability score and an eligibility verdict from Gemini,
    evaluated against versioned rubrics (short-term mobilité vs. classic long-term leases).
    Analyses are cache-keyed by an input hash, so identical inputs never trigger a second
    LLM call and rubric changes never silently rewrite past verdicts.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Two-Pass Escalation</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    When a verdict is unclear with low confidence, the case auto-escalates to a second pass with
    extended thinking enabled — deliberative reasoning reserved for the cases that need it.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">AI Reply Drafts</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Replies are drafted from four archetypes — invite to visit, request missing documents,
    polite refusal, or neutral — which the landlord picks, edits, and queues for sending,
    including bulk polite refusals for non-eligible candidates.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Technology Stack</h2>

  <ul class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Frontend</strong>: React 19, TanStack Router, Tailwind CSS</li>
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Backend</strong>: Convex (realtime database and functions)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Extension</strong>: Chrome Extension (Manifest V3)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">AI</strong>: Gemini Flash via the AI SDK, with prompt caching</li>
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Infra</strong>: Vercel, Stripe subscriptions, Resend, Sentry, PostHog</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Key Challenges</h2>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Consistent, Explainable Scoring</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Scores must be trustworthy enough to base decisions on. Versioned rubrics, immutable
    analyses, and input-hash caching keep every verdict reproducible and auditable as the
    rubric evolves.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Scraping Across Platforms</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Rental platforms vary widely in markup and change without notice. Per-platform content
    scripts plus sync-run tracking detect extraction drift before landlords notice missing
    messages.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Project Impact</h2>

  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Locaperle automates a real, repetitive screening workflow end to end — from raw platform
    messages to a ranked, explainable shortlist with ready-to-send replies — packaged as a
    focused freemium SaaS.
  </p>
</ProjectLayout>
